The Andhra University, the University of California, Berkeley, and the State Department of Higher Education on Sunday signed a three-way MoU in the presence of Chief Minister N. Chandrababu Naidu on the setting up of a Centre for Open Innovation with focus on smart citiesâ€™ development.The Chief Minister, who earlier announced the launch of the Open Innovation Centre at AU Y.V.S. Murthy Auditorium, laid the foundation for it.Solomon Darwin, Executive Director of Garwood Centre for Corporate Innovation, Principal Secretary, Higher Education, Sumita Dawra, and Andhra University Vice-Chancellor G.S.N. Raju signed the MoU.Addressing the gathering, Mr. Chandrababu Naidu underlined the importance of speed, skill, and scaling up, and said India had an edge as it could grow with cost effective technologies. He announced that by June every house in the State would get connectivity of 10-15 Mbps with the Rs.320 crore project using electric poles for cables.